<i>to truly
dedicate yourselves...</i>

235
00:17:42,236 --> 00:17:46,263
<i>to finding little ways to
putting that magic, that spark...</i>

236
00:17:46,340 --> 00:17:48,535
back into your marriage.

237
00:17:48,609 --> 00:17:52,545
When we think of
romance and marriage,

238
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:56,640
<i>what is the first thought that
comes into your mind? Divorce!</i>

239
00:17:56,717 --> 00:18:00,414
Remember when counselors used to tell
you to wrap yourself in cellophane...

240
00:18:00,488 --> 00:18:02,683
To put a little charge
into your marriage?

241
00:18:02,757 --> 00:18:05,555
Do we really pay
for these lectures?

242
00:18:05,626 --> 00:18:08,322
<i>You can see,
it is truly up to you...</i>

243
00:18:08,396 --> 00:18:11,888
<i>to put romance back
into your relationship.</i>

244
00:18:18,939 --> 00:18:21,407
<i>Oh, yeah</i>

245
00:18:21,475 --> 00:18:24,672
<i>Da-na-na
da-na-na-na</i>

246
00:18:24,745 --> 00:18:29,808
<i>As I walk this land
of broken dreams</i>

247
00:18:29,884 --> 00:18:34,321
<i>I have visions
of many things</i>

248
00:18:34,388 --> 00:18:37,482
<i>Happiness
Hi, honey.</i>

249
00:18:37,558 --> 00:18:39,526
<i>Is just an illusion</i>

250
00:18:39,593 --> 00:18:41,561
Evelyn, have you gone insane?

251
00:18:41,629 --> 00:18:43,563
<i>My God,
people can see you!</i>

252
00:18:43,631 --> 00:18:45,690
<i>What if I had been
the paperboy?</i>

253
00:18:45,766 --> 00:18:47,529
Get in there!

254
00:18:47,601 --> 00:18:50,399
<i>What are you
thinking about?</i>

255
00:18:51,205 --> 00:18:54,538
<i>Evelyn?</i>

256
00:18:54,608 --> 00:18:56,906
Evelyn!
Oh.

257
00:18:56,977 --> 00:19:00,936
You know, what we really need
instead of this baloney...

258
00:19:01,015 --> 00:19:05,076
Is an assertiveness training
class for Southern women.

259
00:19:05,152 --> 00:19:08,713
But that's a contradiction
in terms, isn't it?

260
00:19:08,789 --> 00:19:12,020
Especially you, sweetheart.
You're livin' in the Dark Ages.

261
00:19:13,861 --> 00:19:19,094
<i>The roots of love
grow all around</i>

262
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:24,001
<i>But the leaves
they come tumblin'down</i>

263
00:19:24,071 --> 00:19:29,099
<i>Every day, heartaches
grow a little stronger</i>

264
00:19:29,176 --> 00:19:34,170
<i>I can't stand this pain
much longer</i>

265
00:19:35,282 --> 00:19:37,876
Hi, honey. I need one of those. Hi!

266
00:19:37,952 --> 00:19:40,716
Mmm, you smell good too.

267
00:19:40,788 --> 00:19:42,813
I need one of these.

268
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:45,825
Oh, this looks good! Uh-huh.

269
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:47,828
Yes, indeedy.

270
00:19:47,896 --> 00:19:52,959
<i>Always movin'
but goin'nowhere</i>

271
00:19:53,034 --> 00:19:56,936
<i>[Indistinct]</i>

272
00:19:57,005 --> 00:19:59,974
Ed.

273
00:20:01,676 --> 00:20:03,837
<i>Why don't you come in
and sit down at the table...</i>

274
00:20:03,912 --> 00:20:07,848
and have dinner with me? I'm
sorry. The game's almost over.

275
00:20:07,916 --> 00:20:10,749
I just want to see a little bit
of it. Why you so dressed up?

276
00:20:10,819 --> 00:20:13,310
Honey, don't get in the way.
Scoot over a bit.

277
00:20:17,459 --> 00:20:19,017
Ed?

278
00:20:19,094 --> 00:20:22,086
If I'd answered the door
wearing only cellophane,

279
00:20:22,164 --> 00:20:25,463
would you still be
watching the baseball game?

280
00:20:25,534 --> 00:20:29,265
No, honey. I'd probably be
checking you into a looney bin.

281
00:20:51,593 --> 00:20:55,825
<i>Hi, sugar.</i>

282
00:20:55,897 --> 00:20:57,831
<i>How's my dumplin'?
Trick or treat!</i>

283
00:20:57,899 --> 00:20:59,833
<i>You're not gonna throw
them hissy-fits, are you?</i>

284
00:20:59,901 --> 00:21:03,132
<i>Happy Halloween!
Oh, no. No, no, no!</i>

285
00:21:03,205 --> 00:21:05,298
<i>You're meaner than a damn snake.</i>

286
00:21:05,373 --> 00:21:07,364
I'm glad you're feeling better.

287
00:21:07,442 --> 00:21:10,673
<i>Get back in bed. Good thing
your eyesight's failing.</i>

288
00:21:20,322 --> 00:21:23,450
Hey!
Mmm. Oh.

289
00:21:23,525 --> 00:21:26,926
Hey. I was hopin' you'd be here.

290
00:21:26,995 --> 00:21:31,056
My roommate, Mrs. Otis,
said I could visit her family,

291
00:21:31,132 --> 00:21:33,066
but I said, "Thank you kindly,

292
00:21:33,134 --> 00:21:35,762
but I think I might have
my own visitor."

293
00:21:35,837 --> 00:21:37,828
And here you are.

294
00:21:37,906 --> 00:21:40,170
Well, sit down.
Thank you.

295
00:21:40,242 --> 00:21:43,769
And doughnuts to boot!
You can't beat that.

296
00:21:43,845 --> 00:21:46,678
Well, help yourself, Mrs.
Threadgoode. Thank you.

297
00:21:47,415 --> 00:21:48,439
How's your friend?

298
00:21:48,517 --> 00:21:50,508
Mrs. Otis?
Uh-huh.

299
00:21:50,585 --> 00:21:53,520
Well, not so good.
Oh.

300
00:21:53,588 --> 00:21:56,318
Looks like I won't be
gettin' home for quite a while,

301
00:21:56,391 --> 00:21:59,827
and I sure miss it.

302
00:21:59,895 --> 00:22:03,160
Funny what you miss
when you're away from home.

303
00:22:03,231 --> 00:22:05,631
I miss the smell of coffee...

304
00:22:05,700 --> 00:22:08,498
And bacon fryin'.

305
00:22:08,570 --> 00:22:13,064
Oh, what I wouldn't give for a
plate of fried green tomatoes...

306
00:22:13,141 --> 00:22:15,837
Like we used to have
at the cafe.

307
00:22:15,911 --> 00:22:18,311
Ooh!

308
00:22:21,850 --> 00:22:24,910
I never told you about the cafe, did I?

309
00:22:24,986 --> 00:22:26,920
No, ma'am.

310
00:22:26,988 --> 00:22:31,584
Oh, well...
now let me back up a bit.

311
00:22:31,660 --> 00:22:36,893
<i>You see, ldgie never
quite got over losing Buddy.</i>

312
00:22:39,234 --> 00:22:42,294
<i>She hardly
ever come home.</i>

313
00:22:42,370 --> 00:22:45,237
<i>Only Big George
knew how to find her.</i>

314
00:22:45,307 --> 00:22:50,040
<i>She just didn't seem to care
about anythin'anymore.</i>

315
00:22:50,111 --> 00:22:52,045
<i>Then, one summer day,</i>

316
00:22:52,113 --> 00:22:55,083
<i>her mama sent for her.</i>

317
00:22:55,151 --> 00:22:57,085
<i>Like they say,</i>

318
00:22:57,153 --> 00:23:00,645
<i>God never shuts one door
without opening another.</i>

319
00:23:00,723 --> 00:23:04,352
<i>That was also the day ldgie
met Frank Bennett, Mama!</i>

320
00:23:04,427 --> 00:23:07,157
<i>The man whose murder
got her arrested.</i>

321
00:23:07,229 --> 00:23:11,256
Well, hello there, miss.
And who might you be?

322
00:23:12,335 --> 00:23:14,826
Towanda to you.
Who are you?

323
00:23:14,904 --> 00:23:19,136
Oh, Frank Bennett's
the name, Miss Towanda.

324
00:23:19,208 --> 00:23:23,201
I must say you are lookin'
mighty fine today.

325
00:23:23,279 --> 00:23:25,270
You a politician...

326
00:23:25,348 --> 00:23:28,545
Or does lying
just run in your family?

327
00:23:29,885 --> 00:23:32,547
<i>Mama!</i>

328
00:23:32,622 --> 00:23:34,487
Well, there you are!

329
00:23:34,557 --> 00:23:37,549
<i>Well, it's about time,
ldgie.</i>

330
00:23:40,363 --> 00:23:43,264
If you don't look like
the wild man of Borneo.

331
00:23:43,332 --> 00:23:46,927
Here you go. Well, thank you.

332
00:23:47,003 --> 00:23:49,335
Guess who's here?
Who?

333
00:23:49,405 --> 00:23:52,067
Ruth. She's stayin'
with us this summer...

334
00:23:52,141 --> 00:23:55,542
And will be in charge of all the young
people's activities at the church.

335
00:23:55,611 --> 00:24:00,378
Is that why you wanted to see me?
We have so many things planned.

336
00:24:00,449 --> 00:24:02,576
<i>Ruth?</i>

337
00:24:02,652 --> 00:24:06,144
<i>You remember my youngest
child? Of course I do.</i>

338
00:24:06,222 --> 00:24:08,156
Hi, ldgie.

339
00:24:09,725 --> 00:24:12,216
Hi.

340
00:24:15,798 --> 00:24:18,995
Maybe this isn't
such a good idea.

341
00:24:19,068 --> 00:24:21,628
Oh, it's got to work.

342
00:24:21,704 --> 00:24:25,196
<i>Somebody's got to help her. I can't.</i>

343
00:24:25,908 --> 00:24:29,571
Are you sure you want
to go to this river club, Miss Ruth?

344
00:24:29,645 --> 00:24:31,579
These ain't no
churchgoing folks.

345
00:24:31,647 --> 00:24:34,878
<i>I'll do just
fine, George, thank you.</i>

346
00:24:34,950 --> 00:24:37,384
Oh, excuse me.

347
00:24:37,453 --> 00:24:40,752
Is ldgie Threadgoode here
by any chance?

348
00:24:40,823 --> 00:24:43,621
Come on in, honey.
She's right down here.

349
00:24:43,693 --> 00:24:47,129
Here? Okay.
Uh-huh.

350
00:24:47,196 --> 00:24:49,824
I'll see you, Grady Kilgore,

351
00:24:49,899 --> 00:24:51,958
and I'll raise you twenty.

352
00:24:52,034 --> 00:24:54,594
You ain't got nothin'!

353
00:24:54,670 --> 00:24:57,969
<i>Maybe I do and maybe I don't.</i>

354
00:24:58,040 --> 00:25:02,272
Put your money where
your mouth is, Mr. Sheriff.

355
00:25:06,315 --> 00:25:08,943
Well, look what
the cat drug in!

356
00:25:09,018 --> 00:25:12,886
I came to talk to you.

357
00:25:12,955 --> 00:25:15,321
You're gonna have to wait.
I'm busy.

358
00:25:15,391 --> 00:25:17,985
Come on, Grady, this is your
big chance. You in or out?

359
00:25:18,060 --> 00:25:20,494
<i>I'll make you
a rich man.</i>

360
00:25:20,563 --> 00:25:23,555
<i>You just bluffin'again as usual.</i>

361
00:25:23,632 --> 00:25:26,624
I'm afraid you're gonna have to excuse
ldgie. She's goin' home for dinner.

362
00:25:26,702 --> 00:25:28,863
Say good-bye, ldgie.
Where you goin'?

363
00:25:28,938 --> 00:25:33,307
Where the hell you goin' with
my money? We're goin' home!

364
00:25:33,375 --> 00:25:37,311
<i>- Who are you to boss me around?
- The one holdin' your money!</i>

365
00:25:37,379 --> 00:25:39,313
Give it back.

366
00:25:39,381 --> 00:25:41,508
Now, get in the car.

367
00:25:43,385 --> 00:25:46,616
All right, I'll get in the car.

368
00:25:46,689 --> 00:25:49,180
You win!

369
00:25:49,258 --> 00:25:52,227
Come on.

370
00:25:52,294 --> 00:25:53,852
Sucker!

371
00:25:53,929 --> 00:25:55,954
<i>I'll leave when I want!</i>

372
00:25:56,031 --> 00:25:59,832
I don't know how you can break
your mother's heart like you do.

373
00:25:59,903 --> 00:26:02,064
I'm not doin' anything
to my mother.

374
00:26:02,139 --> 00:26:04,699
Oh, no? Why do you think
I'm here for the summer?

375
00:26:04,775 --> 00:26:08,142
Your mother was so worried, she thought I
might be able to talk some sense into you.

376
00:26:08,211 --> 00:26:10,543
<i>But you're too busy
being selfish!</i>

377
00:26:10,614 --> 00:26:13,583
What are you talkin' about?

378
00:26:13,650 --> 00:26:17,347
You're not the only one
who lost Buddy.

379
00:26:17,420 --> 00:26:19,513
We all miss him...

380
00:26:19,589 --> 00:26:22,456
But turning your back on
your family is not gonna help.

381
00:26:24,828 --> 00:26:26,887
What's he got to do
with anything?

382
00:26:26,963 --> 00:26:31,093
<i>Looks like you're the one with
the problem forgetting my brother.</i>

383
00:26:35,472 --> 00:26:37,963
<i>Why, just ten miles away...</i>

384
00:26:38,041 --> 00:26:39,941
<i>down by the river,</i>

385
00:26:40,010 --> 00:26:42,240
<i>there lurks
a den of the devil...</i>

386
00:26:42,312 --> 00:26:46,146
<i>where liquor
and gamblin'...</i>

387
00:26:46,216 --> 00:26:49,049
<i>and sin abide!</i>

388
00:26:49,119 --> 00:26:52,782
Snakes and serpents...

389
00:26:52,856 --> 00:26:55,017
<i>Hey, Scroggins!</i>

390
00:26:55,091 --> 00:26:59,050
You're finally preachin' about
somethin' you're kin to... snakes!

391
00:26:59,129 --> 00:27:02,428
<i>As I said,</i>

392
00:27:02,499 --> 00:27:07,630
snakes and serpents
take many disguises.

393
00:27:07,704 --> 00:27:10,969
<i>Let's turn to page 53
in our hymnal.</i>

394
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:20,072
Yoo-hoo!

395
00:27:20,150 --> 00:27:24,951
Big George thought
I might find you here.

396
00:27:27,824 --> 00:27:32,659
If you give me a chance,
a chance to get to know you,

397
00:27:32,729 --> 00:27:36,460
maybe it'll be fun!

398
00:27:36,533 --> 00:27:39,934
Fun?

399
00:27:40,003 --> 00:27:43,268
Idgie , just spend
some time with me.

400
00:27:43,340 --> 00:27:45,274
Please?

401
00:27:45,342 --> 00:27:47,276
Suit yourself.

402
00:27:47,978 --> 00:27:50,640
<i>You sure you
don't wanna back out?</i>

403
00:27:50,714 --> 00:27:53,911
It's not too late.
I'm sure.

404
00:27:53,984 --> 00:27:56,316
Here, hold this.

405
00:27:58,321 --> 00:28:01,017
Tell me now, you like trains?

406
00:28:01,091 --> 00:28:04,891
Yes.
Good.

407
00:28:04,961 --> 00:28:08,863
We'll get along just fine!

408
00:28:10,367 --> 00:28:13,859
Boy, did we luck out tonight.

409
00:28:16,740 --> 00:28:18,970
Hop in.

410
00:28:19,042 --> 00:28:21,567
Hop?

411
00:28:21,645 --> 00:28:24,671
Oh. Give me
your hand.

412
00:28:24,748 --> 00:28:27,216
Put your foot up there.

413
00:28:36,526 --> 00:28:38,653
Hold that.

414
00:28:39,562 --> 00:28:42,360
Ooo-ooo!
Look at all this!

415
00:28:46,970 --> 00:28:50,531
Don't you think we should get off
the train? It's startin' to move.

416
00:28:50,607 --> 00:28:54,407
No. The fun
just started!

417
00:28:57,747 --> 00:29:00,147
You all right?

418
00:29:00,216 --> 00:29:04,448
Well, sometimes I get
a little dizzy lookin' down.

419
00:29:04,521 --> 00:29:07,218
Don't look down.

420
00:29:20,104 --> 00:29:23,870
What are you doin'?
Come on. Look.

421
00:29:23,941 --> 00:29:26,842
<i>They're throwin'
away food!</i>

422
00:29:30,681 --> 00:29:33,309
You talk about
"give unto others."

423
00:29:33,384 --> 00:29:36,444
Yes, but this food
isn't yours to give.

424
00:29:36,520 --> 00:29:38,681
That's church talk.

425
00:29:38,756 --> 00:29:41,748
I've seen those same people
over at church on Sunday...

426
00:29:41,826 --> 00:29:44,454
Over at the river club every
other night of the week,

427
00:29:44,528 --> 00:29:48,396
doin' anything
but pray. Come on.

428
00:30:04,315 --> 00:30:05,942
<i>More!
Give me some.</i>

429
00:30:31,275 --> 00:30:34,642
Okay, time to get off.

430
00:30:35,279 --> 00:30:37,247
We gotta jump.

431
00:30:37,314 --> 00:30:39,908
Jump?

432
00:30:39,984 --> 00:30:43,044
<i>Yeah, jump. The next stop's
five miles down the tracks.</i>

433
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:45,111
I don't wanna walk
that far back.

434
00:30:45,189 --> 00:30:48,056
Are you crazy?

435
00:30:48,125 --> 00:30:50,491
<i>You're not kiddin'.</i>

436
00:30:50,561 --> 00:30:54,224
Well...

437
00:30:54,298 --> 00:30:56,766
I give up. Jump.

438
00:30:56,834 --> 00:31:00,099
I'll tell Mama I'm not
a good influence on you...

439
00:31:00,171 --> 00:31:02,435
You'll never jump, will you?

440
00:31:04,475 --> 00:31:07,603
Don't say "never" to me.

441
00:31:19,657 --> 00:31:22,421
Towanda!

442
00:31:35,306 --> 00:31:37,900
<i>You all right?
I'm fine.</i>

443
00:31:37,975 --> 00:31:41,536
<i>I'm all right.</i>

444
00:31:41,612 --> 00:31:43,739
Ow!

445
00:31:43,814 --> 00:31:46,146
Does this hurt?

446
00:31:46,217 --> 00:31:48,981
Guess so.

447
00:31:49,053 --> 00:31:51,351
We better get you to
a doc... doctor. Shit!

448
00:31:51,422 --> 00:31:53,515
Which way is it?

449
00:31:53,591 --> 00:31:57,186
About two miles
down the tracks.

450
00:31:57,261 --> 00:31:59,491
All right, let's go.

451
00:32:01,298 --> 00:32:04,790
You'll never be able
to carry me that far.

452
00:32:04,869 --> 00:32:07,565
I know.
Never say never.

453
00:32:07,638 --> 00:32:11,769
I'm not carryin' you.
You're walkin'.

454
00:32:17,716 --> 00:32:22,449
<i>Thank you,
Julian. I owe you one.</i>

455
00:32:34,366 --> 00:32:36,300
Uh. Ow.

456
00:32:36,368 --> 00:32:39,929
Aren't you ready yet?

457
00:32:40,005 --> 00:32:42,098
What?

458
00:32:44,176 --> 00:32:47,236
This doesn't have anything
to do with trains, does it?

459
00:32:48,146 --> 00:32:50,376
You like honey?

460
00:32:50,448 --> 00:32:52,416
Yeah, I like honey.

461
00:32:52,484 --> 00:32:54,475
Fresh honey?
Yeah.

462
00:32:54,553 --> 00:32:58,080
Me too.
There it is.

463
00:32:58,156 --> 00:33:02,354
There what... is?

464
00:33:02,427 --> 00:33:06,295
<i>You'll see soon enough.</i>

465
00:33:10,268 --> 00:33:12,498
Now... stay here.

466
00:33:12,571 --> 00:33:15,506
No matter what happens,
don't move.

467
00:33:15,574 --> 00:33:18,839
What are you gonna do?

468
00:33:53,845 --> 00:33:55,938
Ah.

469
00:34:30,548 --> 00:34:34,143
<i>Here you are, madam.
This is for you.</i>

470
00:34:34,219 --> 00:34:38,588
Why did you do that?
You could have been killed.

471
00:34:38,657 --> 00:34:42,149
I'm sorry.

472
00:34:42,227 --> 00:34:44,923
Don't you want the honey?

473
00:34:44,996 --> 00:34:48,329
I got it just for you.

474
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:50,868
It's all right.
I do it all the time.

475
00:34:50,935 --> 00:34:54,701
I never get stung, honest.

