flooded parts of Whistle Stop.</i>

1176
01:28:57,363 --> 01:29:02,494
<i>That's why Grady's deputies stumbled
onto Frank Bennett's pickup truck,</i>

1177
01:29:02,569 --> 01:29:06,562
<i>and I just knew ldgie'd
never get out of this mess.</i>

1178
01:29:06,639 --> 01:29:10,405
Now, you in or out? Remember,
I didn't take any cards.

1179
01:29:10,476 --> 01:29:12,910
Look at me and
let me see your face.

1180
01:29:12,979 --> 01:29:15,209
Idgie , I have to talk
to you. You're bluffin'.

1181
01:29:15,281 --> 01:29:19,047
Why don't you sit in? I'll deal
you a new hand. Gladys won't mind.

1182
01:29:19,118 --> 01:29:21,211
In private, ldgie.

1183
01:29:21,287 --> 01:29:24,313
Excuse us, Ruth.

1184
01:29:24,390 --> 01:29:28,656
A-ha. I'm just tryin' to teach
you not to fall for any tricks.

1185
01:29:28,728 --> 01:29:31,356
You're doin' a great job.

1186
01:29:40,173 --> 01:29:42,403
What's your hurry?

1187
01:29:42,475 --> 01:29:45,706
And what is so important?

1188
01:29:45,778 --> 01:29:48,008
What's that?

1189
01:29:48,081 --> 01:29:51,414
<i>Somebody found Frank
Bennett's truck in the river.</i>

1190
01:29:51,484 --> 01:29:54,647
What's that got to do with me?

1191
01:29:54,721 --> 01:29:58,680
Officially, you and Big George
are under arrest for murder.

1192
01:29:58,758 --> 01:30:01,659
You're in my custody
until tomorrow.

1193
01:30:01,728 --> 01:30:04,424
I'm supposed to take you to
Georgia first thing in the morning.

1194
01:30:06,499 --> 01:30:08,694
<i>Unless, of course...</i>

1195
01:30:08,768 --> 01:30:11,498
Well, some people have
been known to pack up...

1196
01:30:11,571 --> 01:30:15,974
And sneak out of town
in the middle of the night.

1197
01:30:17,710 --> 01:30:20,270
<i>What about Big George?</i>

1198
01:30:20,346 --> 01:30:23,076
Well, the way I figure it,

1199
01:30:23,149 --> 01:30:26,380
they'd be satisfied
if they had him.

1200
01:30:26,452 --> 01:30:28,511
Idgie , this is serious.

1201
01:30:28,588 --> 01:30:31,182
We're talkin'
murder of a white man.

1202
01:30:31,257 --> 01:30:33,487
Someone's gonna have to pay.

1203
01:30:33,559 --> 01:30:36,392
Nobody wants to hang a woman.

1204
01:30:37,930 --> 01:30:39,921
No deal.

1205
01:30:39,999 --> 01:30:42,593
Idgie , I know how you feel
about Big George.

1206
01:30:42,669 --> 01:30:44,796
Hell, we all do.

1207
01:30:44,871 --> 01:30:48,034
But these just
the facts of life.

1208
01:30:50,476 --> 01:30:52,740
I can't do that.

1209
01:30:52,812 --> 01:30:55,576
Take me to jail if you have to.

1210
01:30:55,648 --> 01:30:58,139
Well, that's what
I thought you'd say...

1211
01:30:58,217 --> 01:31:00,617
'cause you're absolutely,
unconditionally,

1212
01:31:00,687 --> 01:31:05,182
<i>positively the most stubborn
person I've known in my life.</i>

1213
01:31:07,027 --> 01:31:11,726
<i>Idgie  and Big George went
to the county jail in Valdosta...</i>

1214
01:31:11,799 --> 01:31:15,599
<i>to await trial for
the murder of Frank Bennett.</i>

1215
01:31:15,669 --> 01:31:17,796
<i>They didn't have
to wait too long.</i>

1216
01:31:17,871 --> 01:31:21,272
Did you know Frank Bennett? No, sir.

1217
01:31:21,341 --> 01:31:23,741
You mean, you
never met the man...

1218
01:31:23,811 --> 01:31:28,339
<i>whose wife, Ruth, is your
business partner? That's right.</i>

1219
01:31:28,415 --> 01:31:31,248
You never threatened to kill
Frank Bennett at his home...

1220
01:31:31,318 --> 01:31:35,015
In front of his hired man
in June of 1932?

1221
01:31:35,089 --> 01:31:40,117
<i>The same Frank Bennett you did not
know. Oh, that was me, all right.</i>

1222
01:31:40,194 --> 01:31:43,425
<i>I thought you wanted to know if we'd
ever met... and the answer is no.</i>

1223
01:31:43,497 --> 01:31:46,057
<i>Um, I threatened
to kill him,</i>

1224
01:31:46,133 --> 01:31:50,297
<i>but we were never, what you
might say, properly introduced.</i>

1225
01:31:50,370 --> 01:31:54,363
Is it not true that in September
of 1932 you came to Valdosta...

1226
01:31:54,441 --> 01:31:58,275
<i>and took Frank Bennett's wife and
child back to Alabama with you?</i>

1227
01:31:58,345 --> 01:32:00,813
Um... just the wife.
The child came later.

1228
01:32:00,881 --> 01:32:04,339
How much later? The usual. Nine months.

1229
01:32:04,418 --> 01:32:07,285
<i>I suggest that you bribed...</i>

1230
01:32:07,354 --> 01:32:12,656
this poor, weak woman with
promises of liquor and money,

1231
01:32:12,726 --> 01:32:16,457
and she lost control
of her senses momentarily.

1232
01:32:16,530 --> 01:32:19,522
When her husband came back
to get her and take her home,

1233
01:32:19,600 --> 01:32:24,230
you and your colored man
murdered him in cold blood.

1234
01:32:25,439 --> 01:32:27,031
No, sir.

1235
01:32:27,107 --> 01:32:32,374
Well, where were you on the
night of September 30, 1933?

1236
01:32:32,446 --> 01:32:34,744
I was at the town hall
doing a show.

1237
01:32:34,815 --> 01:32:37,909
And after that? I was
at my mother's house.

1238
01:32:37,985 --> 01:32:40,510
Oh, yeah?
Who was with you?

1239
01:32:40,587 --> 01:32:44,921
<i>Just Big George and myself. What about
your mother? Can she confirm that?</i>

1240
01:32:44,992 --> 01:32:47,256
No, sir.
She died a year ago.

1241
01:32:47,327 --> 01:32:49,818
I'm sorry to hear that.

1242
01:32:49,897 --> 01:32:53,594
But do you expect 12 intelligent
men to believe you,

1243
01:32:53,667 --> 01:32:56,295
although one witness is dead and
the other is a colored man,

1244
01:32:56,370 --> 01:32:59,771
known to be a worthless,
no-good, lying nigger?

1245
01:32:59,840 --> 01:33:02,104
You expect these men
to take your word for it...

1246
01:33:02,176 --> 01:33:04,838
<i>Just because
you say so?</i>

1247
01:33:04,912 --> 01:33:09,440
That's right, you gump-faced,
blown-up, baboon-assed bastard!

1248
01:33:09,516 --> 01:33:12,974
<i>One more outburst like that...</i>

1249
01:33:13,053 --> 01:33:16,545
and I'll hold you in contempt
of court. You understand?

1250
01:33:16,623 --> 01:33:19,421
Yes, sir.

1251
01:33:21,128 --> 01:33:24,689
Oh, Lord.
Next witness.

1252
01:33:27,267 --> 01:33:28,734
<i>Did you know
that you were pregnant...</i>

1253
01:33:28,802 --> 01:33:31,737
<i>at the time
you left Valdosta?</i>

1254
01:33:31,805 --> 01:33:33,739
<i>Yes.</i>

1255
01:33:33,807 --> 01:33:37,402
<i>And yet, you tell us
over and over...</i>

1256
01:33:37,477 --> 01:33:42,039
<i>that you went with this
woman... willingly?</i>

1257
01:33:42,115 --> 01:33:46,313
Yes. I wouldn't raise
my child with Frank Bennett.

1258
01:33:46,386 --> 01:33:48,479
<i>But why?</i>

1259
01:33:48,555 --> 01:33:52,753
<i>Did this woman promise you money? No.</i>

1260
01:33:52,826 --> 01:33:55,386
<i>A bigger home?</i>

1261
01:33:55,462 --> 01:33:58,556
No. No.

1262
01:33:58,632 --> 01:34:01,260
<i>Then tell us,
Mrs. Bennett,</i>

1263
01:34:01,335 --> 01:34:03,860
<i>why would a respectable
Christian woman...</i>

1264
01:34:03,937 --> 01:34:06,735
<i>go anywhere with this ldgie
Threadgoode... I object.</i>

1265
01:34:06,807 --> 01:34:08,934
<i>Whose reputation
is known far and wide...</i>

1266
01:34:09,009 --> 01:34:11,240
<i>as a notorious liar
and drunkard?</i>

1267
01:34:11,312 --> 01:34:13,610
<i>- Objection!
- Sustained!</i>

1268
01:34:17,018 --> 01:34:19,316
<i>Why did you leave...</i>

1269
01:34:19,387 --> 01:34:23,346
<i>with ldgie Threadgoode
that day?</i>

1270
01:34:24,759 --> 01:34:28,058
<i>Answer the
question, Mrs. Bennett.</i>

1271
01:34:28,930 --> 01:34:31,956
Because she...

1272
01:34:34,535 --> 01:34:37,129
She's the best friend
I ever had,

1273
01:34:37,205 --> 01:34:39,298
and I love her.

1274
01:34:40,008 --> 01:34:42,909
<i>Thank you, Mrs.
Bennett. That will be all.</i>

1275
01:34:42,977 --> 01:34:45,810
<i>The defense
calls as its last witness...</i>

1276
01:34:45,880 --> 01:34:48,610
<i>the Rev.
Herbert Scroggins.</i>

1277
01:34:49,951 --> 01:34:52,943
Place your right hand
on the Bible, please.

1278
01:34:53,021 --> 01:34:56,218
I brought my own,
if you don't mind.

1279
01:34:56,291 --> 01:35:00,352
You swear to tell the whole
truth and nothing but the truth?

1280
01:35:00,428 --> 01:35:02,419
I do.

1281
01:35:04,465 --> 01:35:08,697
<i>You have
information about the whereabouts...</i>

1282
01:35:08,770 --> 01:35:12,365
<i>of ldgie Threadgoode and her
colored man, known as Big George,</i>

1283
01:35:12,440 --> 01:35:16,206
on the night
of September 30, 1933?

1284
01:35:16,277 --> 01:35:18,245
Yes, sir, I do.

1285
01:35:18,313 --> 01:35:20,747
<i>It has been
suggested here...</i>

1286
01:35:20,815 --> 01:35:24,273
<i>that she and her colored man
were at her mother's house.</i>

1287
01:35:24,352 --> 01:35:28,584
<i>Can you confirm that?
No, sir. That is a lie.</i>

1288
01:35:28,656 --> 01:35:31,386
Oh, shit.

1289
01:35:31,459 --> 01:35:34,690
<i>It has been my
habit to write all the dates...</i>

1290
01:35:34,762 --> 01:35:37,697
<i>of the activities of
the church in my Bible.</i>

1291
01:35:37,765 --> 01:35:42,429
<i>I show that the night
of September 30, 1933...</i>

1292
01:35:42,503 --> 01:35:45,529
was the start of our
annual revival...

1293
01:35:45,606 --> 01:35:48,370
Down at the Baptist campground.

1294
01:35:48,443 --> 01:35:50,536
Sister Threadgoode was there...

1295
01:35:50,611 --> 01:35:54,638
<i>along with her hired man,
George Pullman,</i>

1296
01:35:54,716 --> 01:35:58,846
who was in charge of the
barbecue as he has been...

1297
01:35:58,920 --> 01:36:01,582
<i>for the last ten years.
Objection.</i>

1298
01:36:01,656 --> 01:36:06,184
That doesn't mean anything. Murder could've
taken place any time the next couple of days.

1299
01:36:06,260 --> 01:36:11,288
<i>Have you ever been to one of
our revivals, sir? Well, no.</i>

1300
01:36:11,366 --> 01:36:13,425
Do you attend church
regularly, sir?

1301
01:36:13,501 --> 01:36:15,696
'Course I do.

1302
01:36:15,770 --> 01:36:20,298
<i>Good. Well, maybe if you
attended one of our revivals,</i>

1303
01:36:20,375 --> 01:36:22,741
<i>you'd know
they last three days...</i>

1304
01:36:22,810 --> 01:36:25,142
and three nights, Your Honor.

1305
01:36:27,415 --> 01:36:30,384
<i>Approach the bench.</i>

1306
01:36:30,451 --> 01:36:35,150
Percy, it don't look like
you got a case at all.

1307
01:36:35,223 --> 01:36:37,783
In the first place,
there's no body.

1308
01:36:37,859 --> 01:36:41,124
Second, we got us a preacher
nobody's gonna dispute.

1309
01:36:41,195 --> 01:36:45,393
But, Your Honor... I'm tellin' you.
What you got is a lot of nothing.

1310
01:36:45,466 --> 01:36:48,697
<i>I say Frank
Bennett got himself drunk,</i>

1311
01:36:48,770 --> 01:36:52,934
<i>drove into the river and
was long ago eaten up...</i>

1312
01:36:53,007 --> 01:36:56,170
and I don't give
a good goddamn!

1313
01:36:56,244 --> 01:36:59,702
What we got here is a
case of accidental death.

1314
01:36:59,781 --> 01:37:01,408
Case dismissed.

1315
01:37:01,482 --> 01:37:03,916
Whoo!

1316
01:37:10,858 --> 01:37:13,759
See you in church, Sister?

1317
01:37:14,662 --> 01:37:16,893
Reverend.

1318
01:37:16,965 --> 01:37:21,265
I can't believe he
actually swore on a Bible.

1319
01:37:21,336 --> 01:37:23,270
Well, not really.

1320
01:37:23,338 --> 01:37:25,329
If that judge
had looked closer,

1321
01:37:25,407 --> 01:37:28,467
<i>he'd have seen it was really
a copy of Moby Dick.</i>

1322
01:37:30,512 --> 01:37:34,915
But why did he do it? For the sheer
joy of seeing you in church again...

1323
01:37:34,983 --> 01:37:37,816
Which I suggested to him
might be your penance.

1324
01:37:37,886 --> 01:37:40,514
You didn't promise him,
did you? Yes, ma'am, I did.

1325
01:37:40,589 --> 01:37:42,523
And I never break my word.

1326
01:37:42,591 --> 01:37:46,960
If I live 1,000 years,
I will never forgive you.

1327
01:37:47,029 --> 01:37:51,193
I don't know what's worse,
church or jail.

1328
01:38:02,177 --> 01:38:05,305
There now.
Don't you look pretty?

1329
01:38:05,380 --> 01:38:07,507
Oh, yes, honey.

1330
01:38:07,583 --> 01:38:12,247
You'll have me lookin' like
Ginger Rogers before you're done.

1331
01:38:12,321 --> 01:38:16,553
Don't let Mr. Dunaway see me.
He's liable to go wild.

1332
01:38:18,060 --> 01:38:21,291
I'm glad to see
you're in a good mood.

1333
01:38:21,363 --> 01:38:24,491
You've slimmed down quite a bit
in the last few weeks.

1334
01:38:24,566 --> 01:38:28,866
I'm just so happy Big George
and ldgie got off.

1335
01:38:28,937 --> 01:38:31,929
I would have killed Frank
Bennett if I could've.

1336
01:38:32,007 --> 01:38:34,532
Did anybody really
think she did it?

1337
01:38:34,610 --> 01:38:37,238
Some said yes, some said no.

1338
01:38:37,312 --> 01:38:40,440
'Course the only one who really
knew was Frank Bennett.

1339
01:38:40,516 --> 01:38:45,920
And you know what they say.
Dead men tell no tales.

1340
01:38:46,588 --> 01:38:48,886
<i>Towanda-a-a!</i>

1341
01:39:12,181 --> 01:39:15,207
Evelyn, what in the hell
are you doing?

1342
01:39:15,284 --> 01:39:18,185
I need some light and air.

1343
01:39:18,253 --> 01:39:21,450
Why don't you take one of
your walks or your jog...

1344
01:39:21,523 --> 01:39:25,050
Or whatever it is you do?

1345
01:39:25,127 --> 01:39:28,028
There's no dinner either!

1346
01:39:28,096 --> 01:39:32,533
Ed, you have any idea why I've
been goin' to all these classes?

1347
01:39:32,601 --> 01:39:36,128
<i>No. I've been trying
to save our marriage.</i>

1348
01:39:36,205 --> 01:39:38,230
What's the point
of my tryin'...

1349
01:39:38,307 --> 01:39:42,971
If you're gonna sit on
your butt drinking beer...

1350
01:39:43,045 --> 01:39:45,878
And watching baseball,
basketball, football...

1351
01:39:45,948 --> 01:39:49,076
Bowling and hockey and golf...

1352
01:39:49,151 --> 01:39:53,019
<i>and Challenge
of the Gladiators?</i>

1353
01:39:58,727 --> 01:40:03,255
<i>Mrs. Couch, I'm Sue,
Mrs. Otis'daughter-in-law.</i>

1354
01:40:03,332 --> 01:40:06,768
How are you? I've heard about
you from Mrs. Threadgoode.

1355
01:40:06,835 --> 01:40:10,532
She is so sweet. She's been
lookin' after my mother-in-law.

1356
01:40:10,606 --> 01:40:13,370
Now, how is Mrs. Otis doin', by the way?

1357
01:40:13,442 --> 01:40:17,902
Much better, thank you. It takes
time getting used to a strange place.

1358
01:40:17,980 --> 01:40:22,007
I'm glad to hear it. Mrs.
Threadgoode's been anxious to get home.

1359
01:40:22,084 --> 01:40:26,283
Mrs. Couch, Mrs. Threadgoode
doesn't have a house anymore.

1360
01:40:26,356 --> 01:40:29,814
They tore that down. What?

1361
01:40:29,892 --> 01:40:34,124
They had to. It was falling
apart, and it was condemned.

1362
01:40:34,197 --> 01:40:37,132
Oh, no.

1363
01:40:37,200 --> 01:40:41,398
<i>Does she know that? No, well, we
didn't see any point in telling her.</i>

1364
01:40:41,471 --> 01:40:43,962
<i>It would just break her heart,
poor old thing.</i>

1365
01:40:44,040 --> 01:40:47,976
But I am so glad
I got a chance to meet you.

1366
01:40:48,044 --> 01:40:51,241
You take care of yourself now.
Bye-bye.

1367
01:42:01,217 --> 01:42:03,515
Oh, Evelyn, hey!

1368
01:42:03,586 --> 01:42:06,054
Hey.

1369
01:42:06,122 --> 01:42:08,488
Do you like my roses?

1370
01:42:08,558 --> 01:42:11,891
Since I can't get home
to look at my own roses...

1371
01:42:11,961 --> 01:42:14,327
I made myself a paper garden.

1372
01:42:14,397 --> 01:42:17,889
<i>Got everything but the
bugs. They're lovely.</i>

1373
01:42:17,967 --> 01:42:21,232
You been here long?
Happy birthday!

1374
01:42:21,304 --> 01:42:23,795
Oh! I shouldn't have woken you up.

1375
01:42:23,873 --> 01:42:28,139
'Course you should've. Don't you never let
me sleep through a visitor's day, honey.

1376
01:42:28,211 --> 01:42:32,944
I look forward to them all
week. So do I, Mrs. Threadgoode.

1377
01:42:33,015 --> 01:42:36,348
Oh! I can't
believe you remembered.

1378
01:42:36,419 --> 01:42:40,617
You made me
fried green tomatoes!

1379
01:42:43,059 --> 01:42:45,084
Mmm!
They're delicious.

1380
01:42:45,161 --> 01:42:48,494
It's your recipe. Are they
cold? No. They're just the way...

1381
01:42:48,564 --> 01:42:52,830
We used to have 'em at
the Whistle Stop Cafe. Mmm!

1382
01:42:52,902 --> 01:42:56,838
You couldn't be sweeter to me
if you was my own daughter.

1383
01:42:56,906 --> 01:42:59,067
Here's your napkin.

1384
01:42:59,142 --> 01:43:01,167
And wait-wait-wait.

1385
01:43:01,244 --> 01:43:03,804
Queen, queen.

1386
01:43:06,983 --> 01:43:11,113
You know, I don't feel 83.

1387
01:43:11,187 --> 01:43:15,317
It sorta slipped up on me.

1388
01:43:17,427 --> 01:43:20,863
I never expected
to live this long.

1389
01:43:20,930 --> 01:43:26,527
'Course, the Lord takes us home
when he wants us.

1390
01:43:35,546 --> 01:43:39,175
Are you all right?

1391
01:43:39,249 --> 01:43:41,581
I was thinking about Ruth.

1392
01:43:41,652 --> 01:43:44,450
After the trial was over,

1393
01:43:44,521 --> 01:43:46,716
everything went back
to normal...

1394
01:43:46,790 --> 01:43:50,556
<i>till that fall
when Ruth lost her appetite.</i>

1395
01:43:50,627 --> 01:43:53,187
<i>By the time Doc Hadley
looked at her,</i>

1396
01:43:53,263 --> 01:43:57,461
<i>he said the cancer was so bad
she only had a couple of weeks.</i>

1397
01:43:57,534 --> 01:44:00,264
<i>Well, we moved her
to the Threadgoode house...</i>

1398
01:44:00,337 --> 01:44:05,172
<i>and put her downstairs
so she'd be more comfortable.</i>

1399
01:44:05,242 --> 01:44:09,736
