1555
01:55:44,243 --> 01:55:46,108
Well, why are you...

1556
01:55:46,179 --> 01:55:49,148
Puttin' up this wall
where you just tore one down?

1557
01:55:49,215 --> 01:55:52,343
Well...
I changed my mind.

1558
01:55:52,418 --> 01:55:55,183
I don't mean to seem
dense or anything,

1559
01:55:55,255 --> 01:55:59,487
but what's changed?
The air and the light.

1560
01:56:01,862 --> 01:56:04,456
Ed...
Hmm?

1561
01:56:04,531 --> 01:56:06,999
You remember how
you used to tell me...

1562
01:56:07,067 --> 01:56:09,797
You always wanted
two women in your house?

1563
01:56:09,870 --> 01:56:12,168
Oh, God.

1564
01:56:12,239 --> 01:56:13,900
Yeah.

1565
01:56:13,974 --> 01:56:15,999
Well...

1566
01:56:16,076 --> 01:56:19,011
What if I was
the younger of the two?

1567
01:56:19,079 --> 01:56:22,606
I don't believe
I get your drift.

1568
01:56:22,683 --> 01:56:27,211
I want something more than I've
ever wanted anything before.

1569
01:56:27,287 --> 01:56:30,051
I want to bring
Mrs. Threadgoode...

1570
01:56:30,123 --> 01:56:32,318
To our home.

1571
01:56:32,392 --> 01:56:35,020
I want her
to live here with us.

1572
01:56:35,095 --> 01:56:37,586
I want to give her the love
she's given me.

1573
01:56:37,664 --> 01:56:41,828
You're kiddin' me,
aren't you? I'm absolutely serious.

1574
01:56:41,902 --> 01:56:46,737
That's why I'm puttin' the
wall to Kyle's room back up.

1575
01:56:46,807 --> 01:56:49,867
Well, honey, this isn't
something you're just go and do.

1576
01:56:49,943 --> 01:56:52,605
