1577
01:56:52,679 --> 01:56:55,910
What if she got sick?
Who's gonna take care of her?

1578
01:56:55,983 --> 01:56:57,678
I will!

1579
01:56:57,751 --> 01:56:59,742
I can't leave her
in that place.

1580
01:56:59,820 --> 01:57:03,722
She's not a stray cat.
Hell, she isn't even family.

1581
01:57:03,790 --> 01:57:06,850
She's family to me.
Now, Evelyn.

1582
01:57:07,694 --> 01:57:10,754
<i>Evelyn?</i>

1583
01:57:10,831 --> 01:57:12,696
<i>Honey?</i>

1584
01:57:12,766 --> 01:57:14,757
<i>Ah, look...</i>

1585
01:57:14,835 --> 01:57:19,067
have you mentioned this
harebrained idea to her?

1586
01:57:19,139 --> 01:57:22,199
Not yet.
Well, good!

1587
01:57:22,276 --> 01:57:24,744
Then we'll just pretend
it never happened.

1588
01:57:24,811 --> 01:57:27,837
I'm making my own money.
I'll pay for everything.

1589
01:57:27,914 --> 01:57:31,475
You don't have to do a thing.

1590
01:57:31,551 --> 01:57:34,042
Evelyn...

1591
01:57:34,121 --> 01:57:36,589
It's never gonna happen.

1592
01:57:36,657 --> 01:57:39,319
So just forget about it.

1593
01:57:40,927 --> 01:57:43,691
Don't you ever
say "never" to me.

1594
01:57:52,639 --> 01:57:55,437
Someone helped put a mirror
up in front of my face,

1595
01:57:55,509 --> 01:57:58,103
and I didn't like
what I saw one bit.

1596
01:57:58,178 --> 01:58:02,012
You know what I did?
I changed.

1597
01:58:02,082 --> 01:58:05,984
And that someone...
was Mrs. Threadgoode.

1598
01:58:06,053 --> 01:58:10,547
She needs my love and care,
and I'm gonna give it to her.

1599
01:58:12,326 --> 01:58:15,955
If you'll excuse me,
I have to go to the gym.

1600
01:58:20,901 --> 01:58:23,927
And if you won't listen
to reason...

1601
01:58:24,004 --> 01:58:27,633
There's always Towanda.

1602
01:58:42,422 --> 01:58:45,391
Hey, Nin...

1603
01:58:48,061 --> 01:58:51,087
What are you doing?

1604
01:58:51,164 --> 01:58:53,894
Those are her things,
Mrs. Threadgoode's things!

1605
01:58:53,967 --> 01:58:57,061
What are you doing in here?
Where's Mrs. Threadgoode? Who?

1606
01:58:57,137 --> 01:58:59,971
Mrs. Threadgoode! The woman
who lives here. Are you deaf?

1607
01:59:00,041 --> 01:59:02,942
I'm sorry, miss.
All they told me...

1608
01:59:03,010 --> 01:59:07,208
Was that the woman who lived
in here died this morning.

1609
01:59:09,083 --> 01:59:11,210
Oh, my God!

1610
01:59:11,285 --> 01:59:15,619
Wha... What
are you sayin'?

1611
01:59:15,690 --> 01:59:17,851
<i>She died early
this morning.</i>

1612
01:59:17,925 --> 01:59:22,259
<i>They were shorthanded so they asked
me to take all this stuff down.</i>

1613
01:59:22,330 --> 01:59:24,821
<i>That's all I know.</i>

1614
01:59:44,218 --> 01:59:46,152
Stop that!

1615
01:59:46,220 --> 01:59:48,586
What is the matter
with you people?

1616
01:59:48,656 --> 01:59:51,591
Can't you wait a goddamn day,
for Chrissake?

1617
01:59:51,659 --> 01:59:54,651
Do you have no respect?
These are her things!

1618
01:59:54,729 --> 01:59:58,893
I'm sorry, but they told me to get
this room ready for another patient.

1619
01:59:58,966 --> 02:00:02,163
She may be just
another patient to you,

1620
02:00:02,236 --> 02:00:06,332
but she was my friend,
and I loved her. I'm sorry.

1621
02:00:06,407 --> 02:00:08,341
I'm just following orders.

1622
02:00:08,409 --> 02:00:11,344
